<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c330_25"> 
<div id="v330.25.1"><span class="H1697 s">The word</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H559 s"> came again unto me, saying</span>,</div> 
<div id="v330.25.2"><span class="H1121 s">Son</span><span class="H120 s"> of man</span><span class="H7760 s">, set</span><span class="H6440 s"> thy face</span><span class="H1121 s"> against the Ammonites</span><span class="H5983 s"> †</span><span class="H5012 s">, and prophesy</span> against them;</div> 
<div id="v330.25.3"><span class="H559 s">And say</span><span class="H1121 s"> unto the Ammonites</span><span class="H5983 s"> †</span><span class="H8085 s">, Hear</span><span class="H1697 s"> the word</span><span class="H136 s"> of the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H559 s">; Thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H559 s">; Because thou saidst</span><span class="H1889 s">, Aha</span><span class="H4720 s">, against my sanctuary</span><span class="H2490 s">, when it was profaned</span><span class="H127 s">; and against the land</span><span class="H3478 s"> of Israel</span><span class="H8074 s">, when it was desolate</span><span class="H1004 s">; and against the house</span><span class="H3063 s"> of Judah</span><span class="H1980 s">, when they went</span><span class="H1473 s"> into captivity</span>;</div> 
<div id="v330.25.4"><span class="H5414 s">Behold, therefore I will deliver</span><span class="H1121 s"> thee to the men</span><span class="H6924 s"> of the east</span><span class="H4181 s"> for a possession</span><span class="H3427 s">, and they shall set</span><span class="H2918 s"> their palaces</span><span class="H5414 s"> in thee, and make</span><span class="H4908 s"> their dwellings</span><span class="H398 s"> in thee: they shall eat</span><span class="H6529 s"> thy fruit</span><span class="H8354 s">, and they shall drink</span><span class="H2461 s"> thy milk</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (men: Heb. children)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.5"><span class="H5414 s">And I will make</span><span class="H7237 s"> Rabbah</span><span class="H5116 s"> a stable</span><span class="H1581 s"> for camels</span><span class="H1121 s">, and the Ammonites</span><span class="H5983 s"> †</span><span class="H4769 s"> a couchingplace</span><span class="H6629 s"> for flocks</span><span class="H3045 s">: and ye shall know</span><span class="H3068 s"> that I <i>am</i> the LORD</span>.</div> 
<div id="v330.25.6"><span class="H559 s">For thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H4222 s">; Because thou hast clapped</span><span class="H3027 s"> <i>thine</i> hands</span><span class="H7554 s">, and stamped</span><span class="H7272 s"> with the feet</span><span class="H8055 s">, and rejoiced</span><span class="H5315 s"> in heart</span><span class="H7589 s"> with all thy despite</span><span class="H127 s"> against the land</span><span class="H3478 s"> of Israel</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (hands: Heb. hand) (feet: Heb. foot) (heart: Heb. soul)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.7"><span class="H5186 s">Behold, therefore I will stretch out</span><span class="H3027 s"> mine hand</span><span class="H5414 s"> upon thee, and will deliver</span><span class="H957 s"> thee for a spoil</span><span class="H897 s"> †</span><span class="H1471 s"> to the heathen</span><span class="H3772 s">; and I will cut thee off</span><span class="H5971 s"> from the people</span><span class="H6 s">, and I will cause thee to perish</span><span class="H776 s"> out of the countries</span><span class="H8045 s">: I will destroy</span><span class="H3045 s"> thee; and thou shalt know</span><span class="H3068 s"> that I <i>am</i> the LORD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (a spoil: or, meat)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.8"><span class="H559 s">Thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H3282 s">; Because</span><span class="H4124 s"> that Moab</span><span class="H8165 s"> and Seir</span><span class="H559 s"> do say</span><span class="H1004 s">, Behold, the house</span><span class="H3063 s"> of Judah</span><span class="H1471 s"> <i>is</i> like unto all the heathen</span>;</div> 
<div id="v330.25.9"><span class="H6605 s">Therefore, behold, I will open</span><span class="H3802 s"> the side</span><span class="H4124 s"> of Moab</span><span class="H5892 s"> from the cities</span><span class="H5892 s">, from his cities</span><span class="H7097 s"> <i>which are</i> on his frontiers</span><span class="H6643 s">, the glory</span><span class="H776 s"> of the country</span><span class="H1020 s">, Bethjeshimoth</span><span class="H1186 s">, Baalmeon</span><span class="H7156 s">, and Kiriathaim</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (side…: Heb. shoulder of Moab)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.10"><span class="H1121 s">Unto the men</span><span class="H6924 s"> of the east</span><span class="H1121 s"> with the Ammonites</span><span class="H5983 s"> †</span><span class="H5414 s">, and will give</span><span class="H4181 s"> them in possession</span><span class="H1121 s">, that the Ammonites</span><span class="H5983 s"> †</span><span class="H2142 s"> may not be remembered</span><span class="H1471 s"> among the nations</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (with…: or, against the children of Ammon)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.11"><span class="H6213 s">And I will execute</span><span class="H8201 s"> judgments</span><span class="H4124 s"> upon Moab</span><span class="H3045 s">; and they shall know</span><span class="H3068 s"> that I <i>am</i> the LORD</span>.</div> 
<div id="v330.25.12"><span class="H559 s">Thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H123 s">; Because that Edom</span><span class="H6213 s"> hath dealt</span><span class="H1004 s"> against the house</span><span class="H3063 s"> of Judah</span><span class="H5358 s"> by taking</span><span class="H5359 s"> vengeance</span><span class="H816 s">, and hath greatly</span><span class="H816 s"> offended</span><span class="H5358 s">, and revenged</span> himself upon them; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (by…: Heb. by revenging revengement)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.13"><span class="H559 s">Therefore thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H5186 s">; I will also stretch out</span><span class="H3027 s"> mine hand</span><span class="H123 s"> upon Edom</span><span class="H3772 s">, and will cut off</span><span class="H120 s"> man</span><span class="H929 s"> and beast</span><span class="H5414 s"> from it; and I will make</span><span class="H2723 s"> it desolate</span><span class="H8487 s"> from Teman</span><span class="H1719 s">; and they of Dedan</span><span class="H5307 s"> shall fall</span><span class="H2719 s"> by the sword</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (they…: or, they shall fall by the sword unto Dedan)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.14"><span class="H5414 s">And I will lay</span><span class="H5360 s"> my vengeance</span><span class="H123 s"> upon Edom</span><span class="H3027 s"> by the hand</span><span class="H5971 s"> of my people</span><span class="H3478 s"> Israel</span><span class="H6213 s">: and they shall do</span><span class="H123 s"> in Edom</span><span class="H639 s"> according to mine anger</span><span class="H2534 s"> and according to my fury</span><span class="H3045 s">; and they shall know</span><span class="H5360 s"> my vengeance</span><span class="H5002 s">, saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span>.</div> 
<div id="v330.25.15"><span class="H559 s">Thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H6430 s">; Because the Philistines</span><span class="H6213 s"> have dealt</span><span class="H5360 s"> by revenge</span><span class="H5358 s">, and have taken</span><span class="H5359 s"> vengeance</span><span class="H7589 s"> with a despiteful</span><span class="H5315 s"> heart</span><span class="H4889 s">, to destroy</span><span class="H5769 s"> <i>it</i> for the old</span><span class="H342 s"> hatred</span>; <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for the…: or, with perpetual hatred)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.16"><span class="H559 s">Therefore thus saith</span><span class="H136 s"> the Lord</span><span class="H3069 s"> GOD</span><span class="H5186 s">; Behold, I will stretch out</span><span class="H3027 s"> mine hand</span><span class="H6430 s"> upon the Philistines</span><span class="H3772 s">, and I will cut off</span><span class="H3774 s"> the Cherethims</span><span class="H6 s">, and destroy</span><span class="H7611 s"> the remnant</span><span class="H3220 s"> of the sea</span><span class="H2348 s"> coast</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (sea coast: or, haven of the sea)</span></div> 
<div id="v330.25.17"><span class="H6213 s">And I will execute</span><span class="H1419 s"> great</span><span class="H5360 s"> vengeance</span><span class="H2534 s"> upon them with furious</span><span class="H8433 s"> rebukes</span><span class="H3045 s">; and they shall know</span><span class="H3068 s"> that I <i>am</i> the LORD</span><span class="H5414 s">, when I shall lay</span><span class="H5360 s"> my vengeance</span> upon them. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (great vengeance: Heb. great vengeances)</span></div></div>

